President Biden welcomed President Rivlin of Israel to the Oval Office. He expressed his commitment to strengthening the relationship between the United States and Israel and emphasized his unwavering commitment to Israel's self-defense. President Biden also mentioned the recent airstrikes targeting Iranian-backed militia groups in Iraq and stated that Iran will never get a nuclear weapon under his watch. He expressed his support for the normalization of relations between Israel and Middle Eastern countries and Africa. President Rivlin expressed his gratitude for the strong friendship between the two countries and their shared values of democracy and liberalism. The meeting concluded with President Biden expressing his intention to visit Israel in the future.